00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,679
in the worst case scenario,

578
00:29:36,679 --> 00:29:38,640
right? What if I didn't choose you?

579
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,039
Would you then choose another girl

580
00:29:40,039 --> 00:29:42,039
just to survive?

581
00:29:42,039 --> 00:29:42,959
I'd go all in.

582
00:29:42,959 --> 00:29:43,240
I'd give everything (to one person).

583
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,640
Everything.

584
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:45,880
You'd rather leave, is that it?

585
00:29:48,679 --> 00:29:50,319
So if by chance I didn't choose you,

586
00:29:50,319 --> 00:29:52,160
and you had to leave the island, what then?

587
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,240
I would...

588
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,199
just go all in.

589
00:29:56,199 --> 00:29:56,919
I'd go all in.

590
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:01,760
But I...

591
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,520
Actually I shouldn't tell you this,

592
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:05,160
because I don't want to pressure you.

593
00:30:06,199 --> 00:30:06,719
Really.

594
00:30:06,719 --> 00:30:08,360
You told me

595
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:09,199
you wouldn't feel pressured.

596
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:11,400
What others tell me

597
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:12,959
won't affect my decisions

598
00:30:12,959 --> 00:30:13,480
Okay

599
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:18,280
I rely heavily on my gut feelings to respond

600
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,360
I am a

601
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:23,319
200% hopeless romantic

602
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:28,480
That's why I'm hesitant to

603
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,719
casually start relationships

604
00:30:30,719 --> 00:30:32,839
Because I feel I fall too easily

605
00:30:33,439 --> 00:30:35,280
In this very moment

606
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:36,520
my feelings for this person

607
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:38,919
intensify rapidly

608
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:47,839
The two of us

609
00:30:47,839 --> 00:30:48,719
I need a moment

610
00:30:48,719 --> 00:30:50,439
One of yours left

611
00:30:50,439 --> 00:30:52,120
All of mine are gone

612
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,679
What do you mean all?

613
00:30:53,679 --> 00:30:54,760
They've all left

614
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:55,520
Zhang Xin

615
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:57,319
Tao Zhiquan left

616
00:30:57,319 --> 00:30:58,079
I have nothing else

617
00:30:58,079 --> 00:31:00,079
Just my steadfast guy now

618
00:31:00,079 --> 00:31:00,640
Alright

619
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,319
Tao Zhi left today

620
00:31:04,319 --> 00:31:07,280
People leave every day, just when we get familiar

621
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,719
Just when you start to understand someone

622
00:31:09,719 --> 00:31:10,640
Then they leave

623
00:31:11,959 --> 00:31:13,439
I used to feel protected by him

624
00:31:13,439 --> 00:31:14,760
Now he's gone

625
00:31:18,839 --> 00:31:20,280
I'm feeling all mixed up inside

626
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:22,880
And then...

627
00:31:30,039 --> 00:31:31,079
Let's eat then.

628
00:31:31,079 --> 00:31:32,120
Let's eat.

629
00:31:33,839 --> 00:31:34,880
Finally, we get to see some meat.

630
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,559
There's meat today.

631
00:31:36,559 --> 00:31:37,959
Alright, let's dig in.

632
00:31:40,559 --> 00:31:42,039
Eat more, Fang Xu.

633
00:31:42,039 --> 00:31:43,280
Their portions are too small.

634
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,199
This is all just for you.

635
00:31:45,199 --> 00:31:45,880
Right?

636
00:31:47,799 --> 00:31:50,559
Why does today's meal feel a bit...

637
00:31:50,559 --> 00:31:51,919
...strange?

638
00:31:51,919 --> 00:31:54,480
Every meal from now on feels a bit odd.

639
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:56,160
Look how intense it is over there.

640
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,079
That looks fun.

641
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:09,799
Eat.

642
00:32:09,799 --> 00:32:10,959
Don't hold back.

643
00:32:10,959 --> 00:32:11,919
I'm really hungry.

644
00:32:11,919 --> 00:32:13,000
I've lost my appetite.

645
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,240
Eat quickly.

646
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:17,120
Or you won't have energy for this afternoon.

647
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,240
I never have energy, every single day.

648
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,799
I feel hopeless before every match.

649
00:32:20,799 --> 00:32:21,640
I genuinely have no strength.

650
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,480
It's fine, you don't need to perform today.

651
00:32:28,199 --> 00:32:28,880
Really?

652
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:29,400
Really.

653
00:32:33,679 --> 00:32:35,240
Can you reach it?

654
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:36,520
I can reach it.

655
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:37,679
Looking down on me?

656
00:32:41,719 --> 00:32:42,880
Seems like it.

657
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:44,120
You can't reach it, can you?

658
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:46,319
You take some first.

659
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:50,520
That's enough.

660
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:59,439
Being "served" like this by two guys

661
00:33:00,799 --> 00:33:03,679
Don’t you think it’s too much pressure?

662
00:33:03,679 --> 00:33:04,719
I’ll keep some distance first.

663
00:33:04,719 --> 00:33:05,880
I think we should relax a bit.

664
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:06,559
Let’s keep some space.

665
00:33:06,559 --> 00:33:07,679
We can’t go overboard.

666
00:33:07,679 --> 00:33:09,480
Otherwise, it’d be awkward, right?

667
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,520
Let me tell you—this is the variety show version of *Burn in Winter*.

668
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:25,640
Is this tasty?

669
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:26,640
This is okay.

670
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:27,839
This chicken is decent.

671
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:30,079
I'm just mechanically stuffing food into my mouth.

672
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:33,799
Please, no more tug-of-war this afternoon.

673
00:33:35,719 --> 00:33:37,600
I'm absolutely exhausted.

674
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:38,839
They're so strong.

675
00:33:41,439 --> 00:33:43,520
You know, I knew from the very beginning.

676
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:45,559
Everyone would assume I'm strong.

677
00:33:45,559 --> 00:33:47,439
But deep down I understood.

678
00:33:47,439 --> 00:33:48,600
My training regimen.

679
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:52,120
wasn't designed for this kind of event.

680
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:53,959
So I was bound to fail.

681
00:33:53,959 --> 00:33:55,559
At first I thought he was super tough.

682
00:33:55,559 --> 00:33:57,240
Turns out he's just a "funny guy."

683
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:58,079
That finishing remark.

684
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,640
I ate a bit too much.

685
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:05,120
I'm off.

686
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:11,079
Did you do your undergrad in China?

687
00:34:11,079 --> 00:34:12,360
Yes.

688
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,319
In Beijing.

689
00:34:13,319 --> 00:34:15,319
So you're very familiar with Beijing.

690
00:34:17,279 --> 00:34:19,799
I only moved within one specific area.

691
00:34:19,799 --> 00:34:21,960
The kind who's never been anywhere else.

692
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:23,640
I don't like it.

693
00:34:23,640 --> 00:34:25,440
Too many people, too much pressure.

694
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:26,559
It feels suffocating.

695
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:29,440
So you usually...

696
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:31,559
